{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
    "chapterNumber": 4,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Chronicles 4 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:1",
      "text": "The sons of Judah: Perez, Hezron, Carmi, Hur, and Shobal.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:2",
      "text": "Re-aiah the son of Shobal was the father of Jahath, and Jahath was the father of Ahumai and Lahad. These were the families of the Zorathites.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:3",
      "text": "These were the sons of Etam: Jezreel, Ishma, and Idbash; and the name of their sister was Hazzelelponi,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:4",
      "text": "and Penuel was the father of Gedor, and Ezer the father of Hushah. These were the sons of Hur, the first-born of Ephrathah, the father of Bethlehem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:5",
      "text": "Ashhur, the father of Tekoa, had two wives, Helah and Naarah;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:6",
      "text": "Naarah bore him Ahuzzam, Hepher, Temeni, and Ha-ahashtari. These were the sons of Naarah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:7",
      "text": "The sons of Helah: Zereth, Izhar, and Ethnan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:8",
      "text": "Koz was the father of Anub, Zobebah, and the families of Aharhel the son of Harum.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:9",
      "text": "Jabez was more honorable than his brothers; and his mother called his name Jabez, saying, “Because I bore him in pain.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:10",
      "text": "Jabez called on the God of Israel, saying, “Oh that thou wouldst bless me and enlarge my border, and that thy hand might be with me, and that thou wouldst keep me from harm so that it might not hurt me!” And God granted what he asked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:11",
      "text": "Chelub, the brother of Shuhah, was the father of Mehir, who was the father of Eshton.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:12",
      "text": "Eshton was the father of Bethrapha, Paseah, and Tehinnah the father of Irnahash. These are the men of Recah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:13",
      "text": "The sons of Kenaz: Othni-el and Seraiah; and the sons of Othni-el: Hathath and Meonothai.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:14",
      "text": "Meonothai was the father of Ophrah; and Seraiah was the father of Joab the father of Ge-harashim, so-called because they were craftsmen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:15",
      "text": "The sons of Caleb the son of Jephunneh: Iru, Elah, and Naam; and the sons of Elah: Kenaz.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:16",
      "text": "The sons of Jehallelel: Ziph, Ziphah, Tiri-a, and Asarel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:17",
      "text": "The sons of Ezrah: Jether, Mered, Epher, and Jalon. These are the sons of Bithi-ah, the daughter of Pharaoh, whom Mered married; and she conceived and bore Miriam, Shammai, and Ishbah, the father of Eshtemoa.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:18",
      "text": "And his Jewish wife bore Jered the father of Gedor, Heber the father of Soco, and Jekuthiel the father of Zanoah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:19",
      "text": "The sons of the wife of Hodiah, the sister of Naham, were the fathers of Keilah the Garmite and Eshtemoa the Ma-acathite.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:20",
      "text": "The sons of Shimon: Amnon, Rinnah, Ben-hanan, and Tilon. The sons of Ishi: Zoheth and Ben-zoheth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:21",
      "text": "The sons of Shelah the son of Judah: Er the father of Lecah, Laadah the father of Mareshah, and the families of the house of linen workers at Beth-ashbea;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:22",
      "text": "and Jokim, and the men of Cozeba, and Joash, and Saraph, who ruled in Moab and returned to Lehem (now the records are ancient).",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:23",
      "text": "These were the potters and inhabitants of Netaim and Gederah; they dwelt there with the king for his work.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:24",
      "text": "The sons of Simeon: Nemuel, Jamin, Jarib, Zerah, Shaul;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:25",
      "text": "Shallum was his son, Mibsam his son, Mishma his son.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:26",
      "text": "The sons of Mishma: Hammu-el his son, Zaccur his son, Shime-i his son.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:27",
      "text": "Shime-i had sixteen sons and six daughters; but his brothers had not many children, nor did all their family multiply like the men of Judah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:28",
      "text": "They dwelt in Beer-sheba, Moladah, Hazar-shual,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:29",
      "text": "Bilhah, Ezem, Tolad,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:30",
      "text": "Bethuel, Hormah, Ziklag,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:31",
      "text": "Beth-marcaboth, Hazar-susim, Beth-biri, and Sha-araim. These were their cities until David reigned.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:32",
      "text": "And their villages were Etam, Ain, Rimmon, Tochen, and Ashan, five cities,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:33",
      "text": "along with all their villages which were round about these cities as far as Baal. These were their settlements, and they kept a genealogical record.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:34",
      "text": "Meshobab, Jamlech, Joshah the son of Amaziah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:35",
      "text": "Joel, Jehu the son of Joshibiah, son of Seraiah, son of Asi-el,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:36",
      "text": "Eli-o-enai, Ja-akobah, Jeshohaiah, Asaiah, Adi-el, Jesimiel, Benaiah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:37",
      "text": "Ziza the son of Shiphi, son of Allon, son of Jedaiah, son of Shimri, son of Shemaiah—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:38",
      "text": "these mentioned by name were princes in their families, and their fathers' houses increased greatly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:39",
      "text": "They journeyed to the entrance of Gedor, to the east side of the valley, to seek pasture for their flocks,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:40",
      "text": "where they found rich, good pasture, and the land was very broad, quiet, and peaceful; for the former inhabitants there belonged to Ham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:41",
      "text": "These, registered by name, came in the days of Hezekiah, king of Judah, and destroyed their tents and the Me-unim who were found there, and exterminated them to this day, and settled in their place, because there was pasture there for their flocks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:42",
      "text": "And some of them, five hundred men of the Simeonites, went to Mount Seir, having as their leaders Pelatiah, Ne-ariah, Rephaiah, and Uzziel, the sons of Ishi;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.4.43",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 4:43",
      "text": "and they destroyed the remnant of the Amalekites that had escaped, and they have dwelt there to this day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
